    <text>
        <body>
            <div style="handwritten" type="letter" xml:id="d.1">
                <head type="title">Cornelis de Schepper to Miklós Oláh (Ljubljana, 28 February
                    1534)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p xml:id="reg.p.1">1. Upon arriving to Ljubljana, he learned that Péter
                            Krusics has raided the Turks and ran off many, and according to
                            Schepper, they cannot keep calm at the frontiers. Nobody knows anything
                            about Ibrahim Pargalı Pasha, and there are no significant Turkish armed
                            forces left in Europe. He does not know anything about Lodovico Gritti’s
                            arrival, although Vespasian of Zara has arrived, they have not met yet.
                            2. He is stuck in Ljubljana because the rivers have flooded: the flood
                            has destroyed bridges, and it is not possible to cross the straights. He
                            sends his regards to Wolfgang Haller as well as some letters to his
                            wife, Oláh should make sure she gets them.</p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb facs="https://www.eleveltar.hu/kereso-portlet/spring/digitalcontent/getcontent/preservica/2789F741-0C0F-4A97-A949-CCACF708F260
                    "/>
                <p xml:id="p.1">Cornelius Scepperus Nicolao Olao suo salutem. </p>
                <p xml:id="p.2">[1.] Ego iam perveni <placeName>Lubianam</placeName>, ubi intellexi
                        <persName>Petrum Crusitz</persName><note xml:id="note.1">Péter Krusics or
                        Petar Kružić (1495–1537) was Captain of Klis, Senj, and a famous defender of
                        Klis until his heroic death in 1537. For more on his life, see <hi
                            rend="smallcap">Jurković</hi> 2007.</note> fecisse excursionem in Turcas
                    et profligasse aliquot illorum centurias. Non satis scio, quo consilio aut
                    ratione, nisi quod praesidiarii isti de limitophore quietem pati non possunt. De
                        <persName>Imbrahimo bassa</persName><note xml:id="note.2">Ibrahim Pargalı
                        Pasha.</note> nihil scitur. Quidam dicunt profligatum illum a
                        <persName>Tagmatz Sciach</persName><note xml:id="note.3">Tahmasp I
                        (1514–1576), the second Shah of Safavid Iran, ruled from 1524 until his
                        death in 1576.</note> Sophy,<note xml:id="note.4">Sophy was the name of the
                        ruler of the Safavid dynasty of Iran (ca. 1501–1736), see <hi
                            rend="smallcap">Floor</hi> 2016.</note> alii nescio quo confugisse.
                    Constat, quicquid roboris Turcarum hic fuit, Europa excessisse. De
                        <persName>Gryti</persName><note xml:id="note.5">Lodovico Gritti.</note>
                    adventu nihil dum certi scio, tametsi advenerit <persName>Vespasianus
                        Iaderensis</persName>;<note xml:id="note.6">Vespasian of Zara.</note> credo
                    certiora vos istic scire, nam in <persName>Vespasianum</persName> non incidi. </p>
                <p xml:id="p.3">[2.] Haesi hic <placeName>Lubianae</placeName> ob summa incrementa
                    aquarum. Adeo enim <placeName>Savus</placeName> et
                        <placeName>Labacus</placeName> et ceteri fluvii dissolutione nivium
                    intumuere, ut pontibus fractis undique montis angustias <milestone unit="pb" facs="https://www.eleveltar.hu/kereso-portlet/spring/digitalcontent/getcontent/preservica/2285F648-9DED-44D8-A4A9-4E91B5A90394
                        "
                    />iter prohibeant. Haec serenissimae reginali maiestati refer me nihil
                    obmissurum, quod ad ipsius maiestatem aut Dominationem Vestram aliquo pacto
                    spectare potest. <persName>Wolffgango Haller</persName> me commendabis,
                    ceterisque dominis et amicis. Litterasque ad carissimam
                        <persName>uxorem</persName><note xml:id="note.7">Anna Isabella (Elizabeth)
                        Donche.</note> meam per fidum tabellarium transmittat, cui me ex animo
                    commendo. </p>
                <p xml:id="p.4">Ex <placeName>Lubiana</placeName> ultimo Februarii 1534.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
